Definition 2.3 Let $\mathfrak{C},\mathfrak{D}$ be bicategories, $\mathcal{F},\mathcal{F}^{\prime}:\mathfrak{D}\rightarrow\mathfrak{C}$ pseudofunctors and $\xi,\zeta:\mathcal{F}\rightarrow\mathcal{F}^{\prime}$ pseudonatural transformations. A modification $\mathfrak{n}:\xi\rightarrow\zeta$ consists of a set of 2-morphism $\{\mathfrak{n}_{X}:\xi_{X}\Rightarrow\zeta_{X}\}$ in $\mathfrak{C}$, indexed by the objects $X$ of $\mathfrak{D}$, satisfying the naturality axiom $\zeta_{2}(f)\cdot(1_{\mathcal{F}^{\prime}(f)}\circ\mathfrak{n}_{X})=(\mathfrak% {n}_{Y}\circ 1_{\mathcal{F}(f)})\cdot\xi_{2}(f)$ for all 1-morphisms $f:X\rightarrow Y$ in $\mathfrak{D}$.
Definition 6.29 Two quadruples $(n,\rho,\beta,c)$ and $(n^{\prime},\rho^{\prime},\beta^{\prime},c^{\prime})$ as in Theorem 6.5 are called equivalent if the following conditions hold: (i) $n=n^{\prime}$, and (ii) there exists a permutation $\sigma\in S_{n}$ such that: (a) $\rho^{\prime}(g)=\sigma\rho(g)\sigma^{-1}$ for all $g\in\pi_{0}(\mathbb{G})$. (b) $\beta^{\prime}(u)=\sigma\cdot\beta(u)$ for all $u\in\pi_{1}(\mathbb{G})$. (c) $[c^{\prime}]=[\sigma\cdot c]$ in $\widetilde{H}^{2}(\pi_{0}(\mathbb{G}),(\mathbb{C}^{*})^{n}_{\rho^{\prime}})$, where $\sigma\cdot c\in C^{2}(\pi_{0}(\mathbb{G}),(\mathbb{C}^{*})^{n}_{\rho^{\prime}})$ is the normalized 2-cochain defined by $(\sigma\cdot c)(g_{1},g_{2})=\sigma\cdot c(g_{1},g_{2})$ (the action of $S_{n}$ on $(\mathbb{C}^{*})^{n}$ is that given by (6.3)).
